🧪 SwiftUI Testing Strategies

SwiftUI is highly testable if you test the right layers.
The key is not testing views directly, but testing state, logic, and behavior.

1️⃣ Test Business Logic Outside Views
❌ Anti-Pattern
struct MyView: View {
    var body: some View {
        Text(calculateValue())
    }
}

✅ Correct
final class MyViewModel {
    func calculateValue() -> Int {
        42
    }
}


Why:
SwiftUI views are value types and difficult to unit test directly.

2️⃣ Unit Test ViewModels (Primary Strategy)
Example ViewModel
final class CounterViewModel: ObservableObject {
    @Published var count = 0

    func increment() {
        count += 1
    }
}

Unit Test
func testIncrement() {
    let vm = CounterViewModel()
    vm.increment()
    XCTAssertEqual(vm.count, 1)
}


Coverage Goal:

State changes

Business rules

Edge cases

3️⃣ Test Async Logic with XCTest + async/await
ViewModel
func loadData() async -> String {
    try? await Task.sleep(nanoseconds: 500_000_000)
    return "Success"
}

Test
func testLoadData() async {
    let result = await viewModel.loadData()
    XCTAssertEqual(result, "Success")
}


Why:
SwiftUI encourages async workflows — tests should match.

4️⃣ Use Dependency Injection for Testability
❌ Hard-Coded Dependency
let service = NetworkService()

✅ Injected Dependency
protocol NetworkServicing {
    func fetch() async -> String
}


Mock in Tests

final class MockService: NetworkServicing {
    func fetch() async -> String { "Mock" }
}

5️⃣ UI Tests for User Flows (Not Logic)

Use XCUITest for:

Navigation flows

Button taps

Screen transitions

Example
func testNavigationFlow() {
    let app = XCUIApplication()
    app.launch()

    app.buttons["Go"].tap()
    XCTAssertTrue(app.staticTexts["Detail View"].exists)
}


Tip:
Assign accessibilityIdentifier to SwiftUI views.

6️⃣ Snapshot Testing (Optional but Powerful)

Use snapshot tests to:

Prevent UI regressions

Validate design consistency

Common tools:

iOSSnapshotTestCase

SnapshotTesting (Point-Free)

Best Use Case:

Design-heavy screens

Marketing UI

7️⃣ Test View State, Not View Hierarchy
❌ Don’t Test

Exact view structure

Modifier order

Layout hierarchy

✅ Do Test

State changes

Output values

Published properties

Rule of Thumb:

If your test breaks because of a layout change, you’re testing the wrong thing.

8️⃣ Use Preview-Driven Testing (Human Testing)

SwiftUI previews are manual tests.

#Preview {
    MyView()
        .environment(\.colorScheme, .dark)
}


Use previews to test:

Dark / light mode

Dynamic type

Localization

Edge cases

9️⃣ Avoid Testing SwiftUI Internals
❌ Don’t Test

@State behavior

body recomputation

SwiftUI diffing

Apple already tested that.

🔟 Recommended Testing Pyramid
UI Tests        → Few
ViewModels      → Many
Business Logic  → Many
